The paper deals with the formalization of second-order functions and theorems in the first-order logic of ACL2, which is a theorem proving system based on first-order logic. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also discusses program refinement, which falls under the category of cs.PL (Programming Languages). Additionally, the paper deals with the construction of executable definitions, which is related to cs.SE (Software Engineering). The paper also discusses the use of uninterpreted functions, which is related to cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory). Finally, the paper deals with the systematic generation of instances of second-order functions and theorems, which is related to cs.LG (Learning).
